<p><b>Peter Ruzicka</b> (August 9, 1947 – October 5, 2003) was a Slovak <a href="/wiki/Computer_scientist" title="Computer scientist">computer scientist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mathematician" title="Mathematician">mathematician</a> who worked in the fields of <a href="/wiki/Distributed_computing" title="Distributed computing">distributed computing</a> and <a href="/wiki/Computer_networks" title="Computer networks" class="mw-redirect">computer networks</a>. He was a Professor at the <a href="/wiki/Comenius_University,_Faculty_of_Mathematics,_Physics_and_Informatics" title="Comenius University, Faculty of Mathematics, Physics and Informatics" class="mw-redirect">Comenius University, Faculty of Mathematics, Physics and Informatics</a> working in several research areas of <a href="/wiki/Theoretical_computer_science" title="Theoretical computer science">theoretical computer science</a> throughout his long career.</p>
<p></p>
